-- BAE Systems holding board meeting over EADS merger plan: source
-- 
-- Tue Oct 9, 2012 12:01pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/10/09/us-eads-bae-board-idUSBRE8980Z320121009

 

 (Reuters) - The board of Britain's BAE Systems ( BAES.L ) met on Tuesday ahead of a pending deadline in talks over a proposed $45 billion merger with Airbus parent EADS ( EAD.PA ), a source familiar with the talks told Reuters. 
 The two companies have until 1600 GMT (1200 EDT) on Wednesday to decide whether to proceed with, or drop, talks on a merger aimed at creating the world's largest defense and aerospace company. (Reporting by  Jane Barrett ; editing by Rosalba O'Brien)